# =============================================================================
# DATABASE CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# The app automatically detects which backend to use based on which env vars
# are set. If both are set, Supabase takes priority.
#
# Choose ONE backend: Supabase (recommended) OR Airtable (legacy)

# --- Option 1: Supabase (RECOMMENDED) üåü ---
#
# Why Supabase?
# ‚úÖ Open source & self-hostable
# ‚úÖ Built-in authentication with Row Level Security (RLS)
# ‚úÖ Real-time subscriptions
# ‚úÖ Free tier: 500MB database, 50,000 monthly active users
# ‚úÖ Safe to expose client-side (publishable key is protected by RLS)
#
# Setup Guide: docs/SUPABASE_SETUP.md
#
# Get your credentials:
# 1. Go to: https://app.supabase.com
# 2. Select your project ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí API
# 3. Copy these two values:
#    - Project URL
#    - anon/public key (also called "publishable" key)
#
# ‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT: Use the "anon" or "publishable" key, NOT the "service_role" key!
# The service_role key is for backend use only and should NEVER be exposed.
#
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
# Use either VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY or VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY (same key, both work)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# --- Option 2: Airtable (LEGACY) ---
#
# Note: Airtable support is maintained for backward compatibility.
# New projects should use Supabase.
#
# Migration Guide: docs/MIGRATION_GUIDE.md
#
# Get your credentials:
# 1. Go to: https://airtable.com/account
# 2. Generate a personal access token with read/write scope
# 3. Copy your base ID from the base URL (appXXXXXXXXXXXXXX)
#
# ‚ö†Ô∏è SECURITY WARNING: Airtable credentials are exposed in the client bundle.
# Only use this for MVP testing with trusted users.
# For production, migrate to Supabase or implement a backend proxy.
#
# VITE_AIRTABLE_API_KEY=patAbcd1234567890...
# VITE_AIRTABLE_BASE_ID=appXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# =============================================================================
# IMAGE UPLOAD (Optional - for camera capture feature)
# =============================================================================
# The app supports two methods for uploading product images:
# 1. URL input - Paste any image URL directly (no upload needed)
# 2. Camera capture - Take a photo with device camera (requires upload)
#
# Upload Strategy:
# - Production (Vercel): Uses Vercel Blob storage automatically
# - Development (Local): Falls back to imgbb.com free image hosting
#
# Setup:
# - For local development: Get a free API key at https://api.imgbb.com/
# - For production: Add BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN in Vercel dashboard
#
VITE_IMGBB_API_KEY=your_imgbb_api_key_here

# Production (Vercel Blob):
# 1. Deploy to Vercel once to provision blob storage
# 2. Go to: Vercel dashboard ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
# 3. Add: BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN (generated automatically by Vercel)
# 4. To test locally: vercel link && vercel env pull .env.local

# =============================================================================
# INVOICE OCR & DATA EXTRACTION (Optional - for automatic invoice import)
# =============================================================================
# Feature: Upload invoice images and automatically extract product data
# Saves 90-95% of manual data entry time (15-40 min ‚Üí 1-2 min per invoice)
#
# How it works:
# 1. Google Cloud Vision OCR extracts text from invoice image
# 2. GPT-4o mini parses the text into structured product data
# 3. Review and edit products before importing
#
# Security: API calls are proxied through Supabase Edge Functions
# to keep API keys secure on the server side.
#
# Cost: ~$0.001 per invoice (extremely affordable)
# - Google Cloud Vision: 1,000 pages FREE/month, then $1.50/1000 pages
# - OpenAI GPT-4o mini: ~$0.0001 per invoice
#
# Setup Guide: docs/SUPABASE_EDGE_FUNCTIONS.md
#
# --- Server-Side Configuration (Supabase Dashboard) ---
# These API keys must be set in your Supabase project settings:
# 1. Go to: https://app.supabase.com ‚Üí Your Project ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Edge Functions ‚Üí Secrets
# 2. Add these two secrets:
#    - GOOGLE_CLOUD_VISION_API_KEY
#    - OPENAI_API_KEY
#
# Get Google Cloud Vision API key:
# 1. Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 2. Create a new project (or select existing)
# 3. Enable "Cloud Vision API"
# 4. Create credentials ‚Üí API key
# 5. (Optional) Restrict key to Cloud Vision API for security
#
# Get OpenAI API key:
# 1. Go to: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# 2. Create new secret key
# 3. Add billing method (pay-as-you-go)
#
# Note: These keys are NOT stored in .env - they're server-side only!
# The app calls Supabase Edge Functions which use these keys securely.

